reasoning_steps: Step 1: Completed Balance Sheet by linking Cash to Cash Flow ending cash, driving A/R, Inventory, and A/P from Income Statement (Revenue/COGS) and working-capital day assumptions (DSO/DIO/DPO), rolling PP&E using CapEx (% of Revenue) and Depreciation (% of prior PP&E), and rolling Retained Earnings using prior RE + Net Income - Dividends/Buybacks; kept other non-driver lines as existing links.

Step 2: Tied Cash Flow by linking Net Income from Income Statement, calculating D&A from Depreciation % * prior-year PP&E, calculating working-capital changes as the negative/positive of Balance Sheet deltas (A/R, Inventory, A/P), setting CapEx as negative Revenue * CapEx %, linking Dividends/Buybacks from Balance Sheet, and setting Debt & other financing equal to the change in total debt (ST + LT) from the Balance Sheet.

Step 3: Validated the model by ensuring Cash Flow ending cash rolls forward from beginning cash plus CFO/CFI/CFF and that Balance Sheet cash references Cash Flow ending cash; confirmed working-capital change signs match Balance Sheet movements.
